When JIRA fails to create an application link, we should have more details as to why the application link fails to create.

Currently on the UI we display:

{noformat}No response was received from the URL you entered. It may not be valid.{noformat}
or 
{noformat}No response was received from the URL you entered - it may not be valid. Please fix the URL below, if needed, and click Continue.{noformat}

While the logs will tell us:

{noformat}javax.net.ssl.SSLHandshakeException: sun.security.validator.ValidatorException: PKIX path building failed: sun.security.provider.certpath.SunCertPathBuilderException: unable to find valid certification path to requested target
 at com.sun.mail.imap.IMAPStore.protocolConnect(IMAPStore.java:441)
 at javax.mail.Service.connect(Service.java:233)
 at javax.mail.Service.connect(Service.java:134){noformat}

 {noformat}Unable to respond to any of these challenges{noformat}

and so on.  Including even these errors messages on the UI would be extremely useful.

